The paper deals with the study of graphs and their properties, which falls under the category of Discrete Mathematics (cs.DM). The graphs studied in the paper are defined on a grid, which suggests that Computational Geometry (cs.CG) may also be a relevant sub-category. The paper also discusses the computational complexity of several graph problems, indicating that Data Structures (cs.DS) and Computational Complexity (cs.CC) may also be relevant sub-categories. Finally, the paper examines the related class of edge-intersection graphs of paths with at most k bends on a grid, which suggests that Graph Theory (cs.GT) may also be a relevant sub-category.
